## 1. Phase 0 — Sequencing and Multi-Agent Protocol

### 1.1 A1 first (blocking, week 1, single agent)

Execute A1 (master CSV freeze + protocol_maturity column) sequentially. **Voies B and C cannot start before A1 completes** because:

- B1 depends on `r20_curated_oof` audit-tagged in master.
- C1 depends on master CSV reconstructability.
- Scenario exporter (A2) reads `protocol_maturity`.

### 1.2 After A1 — three autonomous agents in parallel

User runs **3 separate Claude/Codex agents with isolated context windows** (OQ3). Each agent owns one voie. Synchronization rules:

| Sync mechanism | Path | Owner |
|---|---|---|
| Master CSV (read-only after A1) | `bench/benchmark_master_results.csv` | C |
| Scenario manifests (registry-controlled) | `bench/scenarios/model_registry.yaml` | C (writes) ; A,B (read + propose PR-style diffs) |
| Per-voie results | `bench/scenarios/runs/<preset>/results.csv` | A,B (write own rows) |
| Per-voie status | `bench/<voie>/STATUS.md` | A,B,C each owns one |
| Cross-voie blockers | `bench/SYNC.md` (single file, append-only log) | All |
| Codex review log | `bench/<voie>/docs/CODEX_REVIEWS.md` | All |

**Rules** :

1. Only Voie C writes to `model_registry.yaml`. A and B propose changes via `bench/SYNC.md` entries; C arbitrates.
2. No agent edits another voie's directory. Cross-voie data flows through master CSV + registry only.
3. Each agent ends every session with a `STATUS.md` update + a `SYNC.md` entry if it produced or consumed something cross-voie.
4. Compute coordination: agents declare GPU usage in `SYNC.md` before launching long jobs (4090 local — see §1.3).

### 1.3 Compute coordination (OQ11)

- Local : RTX 4090 (single GPU).
- Available on demand : LAN GPUs via SSH — agent **must ask user before planning a job that requires LAN GPUs**.
- Default scheduling : Voie B (NN training) gets 4090 priority weeknights/weekends. Voie A (CPU-bound mostly) and Voie C run anytime.

